user_info.Images[1].Caption:
Welcome back, #Crew9! The Earth missed you. 

Theirs has been a test of grit, courage and the boundless human spirit. Sunita Williams and the Crew-9 astronauts have once again shown us what perseverance truly means. Their unwavering determination in the face of the vast unknown will forever inspire millions. 

Space exploration is about pushing the limits of human potential, daring to dream, and having the courage to turn those dreams into reality. Sunita Williams, a trailblazer and an icon, has exemplified this spirit throughout her career.

We are incredibly proud of all those who worked tirelessly to ensure their safe return. They have demonstrated what happens when precision meets passion and technology meets tenacity.

(Sharing a photo of a previous meeting with Sunita Williams during one of my USA visits)

@nasa

user_info.Images[8].Caption:
Namaste India and Happy #WomensDay.

I am Dr. @access_anjlee , founder of @samarthyam.cua. Through PM @narendramodi’s social media handle, which I have the honour of taking over today, I want to ignite a spark of transformation, and seek a call to action- forget labels, forget barriers…lets strengthen Sugamya Bharat and make it an important precursor to a Viksit Bharat. 

Let's ensure that every woman, every individual, can navigate their life with dignity and independence. Let us build on the recent gains and improve lives for persons with disabilities. 

Here is more about myself- for over three decades, I've worked on universal accessibility and inclusive mobility. These sectors are integral to creating inclusive spaces. Basis my experience of the recent past, I am positive that accessibility and mobility are no longer remaining only in words but have been seamlessly assimilated with other aspects of governance. 

Research and writing are key passions for me, because this is also how we can drive a positive change when it comes to improving the lives of persons with disabilities. Here too, working towards empowering women with disabilities has been very important for me. I conduct extensive training workshops for government and educational institutions to further this goal. I have worked widely in making schools accessible in India. This is vital because, no one must be denied education just because of lack of accessible infrastructure. 

Recognising the importance of basic needs, I’ve worked on WASH facilities for persons with disabilities and conducted anthropometric studies to better understand the needs of mobility aid users. Our collective success in Swachh Bharat has particularly benefited persons with disabilities. 

Ultimately, I aim to be a leading force in creating accessible and inclusive environments in India, with a deep commitment to empowering individuals with disabilities in partnership with individuals, organisations and governments. The mindset change, combined with positive action on the ground and many policy changes have been encouraging. Today, many women with disabi
user_info.Images[9].Caption:
A financially empowered woman is a confident decision-maker, independent thinker, architect of her own future and a maker of modern India! And, our nation is taking the lead in building financially empowered women.

I, @ajaita , am really delighted to be handling PM @narendramodi Ji’s social media handles on #WomensDay. I am the Founder and CEO of Frontier Markets.

One issue that remained close to my heart was the challenges women face in rural areas. These challenges could be financial, access to infrastructure and more. Thus, I have spent the last two decades to mitigate this. And, I feel proud that not only have I been able to make a difference, I am also seeing many more women rising to the occasion and doing the same.

In 2011, I founded Frontier Markets with a simple belief that if we support our rural women, no force will stop them from achieving the impossible. Our combined efforts have ensured a powerful network of thousands of women who are becoming self-reliant and giving livelihoods to other women.

It is gladdening that over the last few years, there are very meaningful conversations happening on this subject. With things like bank coverage, social security, access to better healthcare and improved sanitation, women are finding it much easier to pursue their dreams and create value for society.

Our emphasis has always been on integrating technology to ensure skilling and financial inclusion of women. It would amaze you all, the ease with which India’s women are adapting to technology. Our ‘Meri Saheli App’ is a small contribution to harnessing tech and AI to help rural women become entrepreneurs. It has also enabled the world to see the strengths of our women in diverse areas like agriculture, healthcare, consumer durables and financial literacy.

Today, our nation can’t be ignored by the world. We are a promising market with an innovative spirit. And, this journey will get even stronger with women’s participation. I will urge all women to become a part of the India Story. A lot of women have shown how to break barriers and achieve this. My own experience says that the sky is the limit. Be self-reliant and give a better life to the future gene
user_info.Images[10].Caption:
मैं अनीता देवी, नालंदा जिले के अनन्तपुर गांव की रहने वाली हूं। मैंने जीवन में बड़े संघर्ष देखे हैं। लेकिन मेरा हमेशा से मन था, अपने दम पर कुछ करने का। 2016 में मैंने खुद स्वरोजगार करने का निर्णय लिया था। उसी दौर में स्टार्ट-अप्स का इतना क्रेज बढ़ गया था। इसलिए 9 साल पहले मैंने भी अपनी माधोपुर फार्मर्स प्रोड्यूसर कंपनी लिमिटेड की स्थापना की।

मशरूम उत्पादन से आत्मनिर्भरता की ओर!
आज मशरूम उत्पादन के जरिये मैं अपने परिवार को आगे बढ़ाने के लिए काम कर रही हूं। मैंने ना सिर्फ अपनी राह आसान की है, बल्कि सैकड़ों महिलाओं को रोजगार के अवसर देकर आत्मनिर्भर भी बनाया है। अब मेरी कंपनी किसानों को खाद, बीज और कीटनाशक जैसी जरूरी चीजों को भी सस्ती दरों पर उपलब्ध कराती है। आज इस कंपनी में काम करने वाली सैकड़ों महिलाओं को, आजीविका के साथ स्वाभिमान का जीवन भी मिल रहा है।

मेरी प्रेरणा – महिलाओं को आत्मनिर्भर बनाना!
बिहार सरकार की जीविका परियोजना और राष्ट्रीय ग्रामीण आजीविका मिशन (NRLM) की मदद से मैंने मशरूम उत्पादन का प्रशिक्षण लिया था। इसके बाद मैंने सैकड़ों महिलाओं को भी मशरूम की खेती से जोड़ा है। अब मेरा सपना है कि गांव की हर महिला अपने पैरों पर खड़ी हो। अभी जो मखाना बोर्ड की स्थापना का ऐलान हुआ है, उसके बाद मैं मखाने से जुड़े काम के बारे में भी सोच रही हूं।

आत्मनिर्भर महिला, आत्मनिर्भर समाज!
मेरे साथ काम करने वाली महिलाओं को आत्मनिर्भर बनते देखना मेरी सबसे बड़ी खुशी है। मैं मानती हूं कि आर्थिक स्वतंत्रता ही महिलाओं के सम्मान और सामाजिक स्थिति को मजबूत करती है। आज जब मेरे साथ की महिलाएं अपने परिवार के लिए कुछ अच्छा करती हैं, तो मुझे इससे सबसे ज्यादा संतोष होता है।

अगर मैंने कर दिखाया, तो आप भी कर सकती हैं!
मेरा मानना है कि अगर मैं ये काम कर सकती हूं, तो ये कोई भी कर सकता है। मेरा देश की सभी बहनों को यही संदेश है कि वो आत्मनिर्भर बनें और अपने साथ साथ अपने परिवार का जीवन बदलने के लिए भी काम करें। अगर आप अपनी लगन और परिश्रम से आगे बढ़ने का प्रण कर लेंगी, तो दुनिया की कोई शक्ति आपको नहीं रोक पाएगी।

#WomensDay
user_info.Images[11].Caption:
Nuclear technology and women empowerment…

I am Shilpi Soni, a space scientist and I am overjoyed to be helming the PM’s social media properties on #WomensDay.

I am from Sagar in Madhya Pradesh. I belong to a very humble background but my family has always been passionate about learning, innovation and culture. After a stint at DRDO, it was a dream come true to work with ISRO, where I have contributed towards design, development and induction of state-of-the-art RF and Microwave subsystem technologies for more than 35 communication and navigation mission of ISRO over the last 24 fruitful years.

What I like about ISRO is that there is no glass ceiling and offers immense opportunities for all, to address complex challenges with innovative solutions thereby making a long-lasting impact. It’s totally onto us, how we convert these chances into opportunities, expand our wings and fly high.

Some of our collective successes make me proud. Pleased to share that ISRO has successfully indigenised highly complex and guarded Space Travelling wave tube technology that is available globally with only a handful of nations. It is a leap forward for India towards achieving Aatmanirbharta in space technology. 

My current assignment includes serving as Associate Project Director for GSAT-22/23 communication payload to cater communication needs for India’s citizens. Earlier, I was fortunate to have been a part of the ISRO delegation to French Guyana, Kourou for the launch of GSAT. It gave me so much satisfaction to see the spacecraft being launched to space, in which I contributed along with a brilliant team.

मेरे साथ काम करने वाली महिलाओं को आत्मनिर्भर बनते देखना मेरी सबसे बड़ी खुशी है। मैं मानती हूं कि आर्थिक स्वतंत्रता ही महिलाओं के सम्मान और सामाजिक स्थिति को मजबूत करती है। आज जब मेरे साथ की महिलाएं अपने परिवार के लिए कुछ अच्छा करती हैं, तो मुझे इससे सबसे ज्यादा संतोष होता है।

अगर मैंने कर दिखाया, तो आप भी कर सकती हैं!
मेरा मानना है कि अगर मैं ये काम कर सकती हूं, तो ये कोई भी कर सकता है। मेरा देश की सभी बहनों को यही संदेश है कि वो आत्मनिर्भर बनें और अपने साथ साथ अपने परिवार का जीवन बदलने के लिए भी काम करें। अगर आप अपनी लगन और परिश्रम से आगे बढ़ने का प्रण कर लेंगी, तो दुनिया की कोई शक्ति आपको नहीं रोक पाएगी।

images.captions[11]:
Nuclear technology and women empowerment…

I am Shilpi Soni, a space scientist and I am overjoyed to be helming the PM’s social media properties on #WomensDay.

I am from Sagar in Madhya Pradesh. I belong to a very humble background but my family has always been passionate about learning, innovation and culture. After a stint at DRDO, it was a dream come true to work with ISRO, where I have contributed towards design, development and induction of state-of-the-art RF and Microwave subsystem technologies for more than 35 communication and navigation mission of ISRO over the last 24 fruitful years.

What I like about ISRO is that there is no glass ceiling and offers immense opportunities for all, to address complex challenges with innovative solutions thereby making a long-lasting impact. It’s totally onto us, how we convert these chances into opportunities, expand our wings and fly high.

Some of our collective successes make me proud. Pleased to share that ISRO has successfully indigenised highly complex and guarded Space Travelling wave tube technology that is available globally with only a handful of nations. It is a leap forward for India towards achieving Aatmanirbharta in space technology. 

My current assignment includes serving as Associate Project Director for GSAT-22/23 communication payload to cater communication needs for India’s citizens. Earlier, I was fortunate to have been a part of the ISRO delegation to French Guyana, Kourou for the launch of GSAT. It gave me so much satisfaction to see the spacecraft being launched to space, in which I contributed along with a brilliant team.

#मुंबई, #अहिल्यानगर, #सोलापूर, #सांगली, #पुणे, #लातूर जिल्ह्यातील उबाठा गटातील विविध पदाधिकाऱ्यांनी आज #शिवसेना पक्षात जाहीर प्रवेश केला. यावेळी या सर्वांचे पक्षात स्वागत करून त्यांना भावी सामाजिक आणि राजकीय वाटचालीसाठी शुभेच्छा दिल्या. 

यात प्रामुख्याने वरळीतील वृत्तपत्र विक्रेता संघाचे २०० आणि तेलगू समाजाच्या ३०० महिलांचा समावेश होता. तसेच अहिल्यानगर जिल्ह्यातील प्रहार जनशक्ती पक्षाचे माजी जिल्हाप्रमुख अभिजित पोटे, उबाठा उप जिल्हाप्रमुख आशिक दहीफळे, संदेश कार्ले, जिल्हा परिषद सदस्य शरद झोडगे, शेवगावचे राष्ट्रवादी काँग्रेस पक्षाचे शहर प्रमुख अमर पुरनाळे यांचा समावेश होता. 

तर सोलापूर, सांगली, पुणे आणि लातूर मधील उबाठा गटाचे माजी संपर्कप्रमुख संजय कोकाटे, जिल्हा समन्वयक सचिन सोनटक्के, मंगळवेढा तालुका संघटक मारुती वाघमारे, सांगली जिल्ह्याचे उबाठाचे जिल्हाप्रमुख संजय विभूते, मनसेचे माजी जिल्हाप्रमुख वैभव कुलकर्णी, जिल्हा संघटक बजरंग पाटील, पुणे जिल्ह्यातील उबाठा उप शहरप्रमुख नरवीर तानाजी मालुसरे यांचे वंशज बाळासाहेब मालुसरे, वडगाव शेरीचे आनंद गोयल, लातूरच्या दलित महासंघाचे जिल्हाध्यक्ष अनंत दोरवे तसेच माजी नगरसेवक, जिल्हा परिषद सदस्य आणि सरपंच यांचा समावेश होता. 

ज्येष्ठ नगरसेवक राम रेपाळे यांच्या पुढाकाराने झालेल्या या पक्षप्रवेशावेळी शिवसेना नेत्या डॉ.नीलम गोऱ्हे, शिवसेना सचिव संजय मोरे, सचिव संजय म्हशीलकर, उपनेत्या आशा मामेडी, वरळीचे विभागप्रमुख दत्ता नरवणकर, प्रवक्त्या प्रा.ज्योती वाघमारे, माजी नगरसेवक पांडुरंग पाटील, प्रवक्ते संजीव भोर पाटील आणि शिवसेनेचे जिल्हाप्रमुख, पदाधिकारी आणि शिवसैनिक मोठ्या संख्येने उपस्थित होते.

विधानभवनातील माझ्या दालनात आज कोल्हापूरमधील आमदारांची विशेष बैठक आज पार पडली. या बैठकीत कोल्हापूर जिल्ह्यातील  आमदारांची आणि लाखो शिवप्रेमींची ही मागणी मान्य करत शिवस्मारकाच्या कामासाठी निधी देण्याचा निर्णय घेऊन तसा जीआर आजच्या आज कोल्हापुरातील आमदारांच्या हाती सुपूर्द करण्यात आला. 

यावेळी आरोग्य मंत्री प्रकाश आबीटकर, आमदार राजेश क्षीरसागर, आमदार चंद्रदीप नरके, नगरविकास विभागाचे प्रधान सचिव असीम गुप्ता, उपमुख्यमंत्री कार्यालयाचे प्रधान सचिव नवीन सोना तसेच इतर वरिष्ठ अधिकारी उपस्थित होते.

‘बीबीसी मराठी’ या डिजिटल वाहिनीच्या वतीने आयोजित करण्यात आलेल्या ‘राष्ट्र महाराष्ट्र’ या विशेष कार्यक्रमात सहभागी होऊन बीबीसी मराठीचे संपादक अभिजित कांबळे यांच्यासोबत राज्याच्या विकासाचे चित्र मांडले. 

महायुती सरकारच्या १०० दिवसांच्या कार्यकाळात सात सुत्रांवर आधारीत काम करून लोकांना दिलासा देण्याचा प्रयत्न केला असल्याचे याप्रसंगी सांगितले. कृषी, शिक्षण, आरोग्य, पायाभूत सुविधा, गुंतवणूक आणि लोककल्याणकारी योजना यांना प्राधान्य देऊन त्यानुसार निर्णय घेण्याचा प्रयत्न केला असल्याचे यासमयी सांगितले. 

आमच्यात कोणतीही स्पर्धा नसून मुख्यमंत्री आणि दोन्ही उपमुख्यमंत्री एकमेकांसोबत काम करत आहोत. त्यामुळे राज्य प्रगतीपथावर असून पायाभूत सुविधा, उद्योग आणि परकीय गुंतवणूक क्षेत्रात राज्य आज देशात आघाडीवर आहे. त्यामुळे जनतेने घरी बसवलेल्यांचा विचार न करता राज्याच्या सर्वांगीण विकासाला आम्ही प्राधान्य दिले असल्याचे याप्रसंगी स्पष्ट केले.

यावेळी बीबीसी मराठीचे पत्रकार विनायक गायकवाड, निलेश धोत्रे, दीपाली जगताप आणि संपादकीय टीमचे सर्व सदस्य उपस्थित होते.

#मुंबई, #अहिल्यानगर, #सोलापूर, #सांगली, #पुणे, #लातूर जिल्ह्यातील उबाठा गटातील विविध पदाधिकाऱ्यांनी आज #शिवसेना पक्षात जाहीर प्रवेश केला. यावेळी या सर्वांचे पक्षात स्वागत करून त्यांना भावी सामाजिक आणि राजकीय वाटचालीसाठी शुभेच्छा दिल्या. 

यात प्रामुख्याने वरळीतील वृत्तपत्र विक्रेता संघाचे २०० आणि तेलगू समाजाच्या ३०० महिलांचा समावेश होता. तसेच अहिल्यानगर जिल्ह्यातील प्रहार जनशक्ती पक्षाचे माजी जिल्हाप्रमुख अभिजित पोटे, उबाठा उप जिल्हाप्रमुख आशिक दहीफळे, संदेश कार्ले, जिल्हा परिषद सदस्य शरद झोडगे, शेवगावचे राष्ट्रवादी काँग्रेस पक्षाचे शहर प्रमुख अमर पुरनाळे यांचा समावेश होता. 

तर सोलापूर, सांगली, पुणे आणि लातूर मधील उबाठा गटाचे माजी संपर्कप्रमुख संजय कोकाटे, जिल्हा समन्वयक सचिन सोनटक्के, मंगळवेढा तालुका संघटक मारुती वाघमारे, सांगली जिल्ह्याचे उबाठाचे जिल्हाप्रमुख संजय विभूते, मनसेचे माजी जिल्हाप्रमुख वैभव कुलकर्णी, जिल्हा संघटक बजरंग पाटील, पुणे जिल्ह्यातील उबाठा उप शहरप्रमुख नरवीर तानाजी मालुसरे यांचे वंशज बाळासाहेब मालुसरे, वडगाव शेरीचे आनंद गोयल, लातूरच्या दलित महासंघाचे जिल्हाध्यक्ष अनंत दोरवे तसेच माजी नगरसेवक, जिल्हा परिषद सदस्य आणि सरपंच यांचा समावेश होता. 

ज्येष्ठ नगरसेवक राम रेपाळे यांच्या पुढाकाराने झालेल्या या पक्षप्रवेशावेळी शिवसेना नेत्या डॉ.नीलम गोऱ्हे, शिवसेना सचिव संजय मोरे, सचिव संजय म्हशीलकर, उपनेत्या आशा मामेडी, वरळीचे विभागप्रमुख दत्ता नरवणकर, प्रवक्त्या प्रा.ज्योती वाघमारे, माजी नगरसेवक पांडुरंग पाटील, प्रवक्ते संजीव भोर पाटील आणि शिवसेनेचे जिल्हाप्रमुख, पदाधिकारी आणि शिवसैनिक मोठ्या संख्येने उपस्थित होते.

#Shivsena #EknathShinde #Maharashtra
@shivsenaofc

दिवंगत कला दिग्दर्शक नितीन देसाई यांचे स्वप्न असलेल्या कर्जत येथील एन.डी.स्टुडिओ हा आता महाराष्ट्र राज्य चित्रपट, रंगभूमी आणि सांस्कृतिक महामंडळाने परिचलनासाठी ताब्यात घेतला असून आज मुख्यमंत्री देवेंद्र फडणवीस यांच्या शुभहस्ते एनडी आर्ट वर्ल्ड या संस्थेस १३० कोटींचा धनादेश देऊन हस्तांतरण प्रक्रिया पूर्ण करण्यात आली. 

यावेळी उपमुख्यमंत्री अजित पवार, सांस्कृतिक कार्य मंत्री ऍड.आशिष शेलार, उद्योग तथा मराठी भाषा मंत्री उदय सामंत, विधानपरिषद सभापती प्रा.राम शिंदे तसेच सांस्कृतिक कार्य विभागाचे अप्पर मुख्य सचिव विकास खारगे आणि इतर सदस्य उपस्थित होते.

#EknathShinde #Maharashtra

#कोल्हापूर जिल्ह्यातील ऐतिहासिक पन्हाळा किल्ल्यावरील शिवस्मारकाच्या उभारणीसाठी नगरविकास विभागाच्या माध्यमातून १० कोटींचा निधी मंजूर करण्याचा निर्णय आज घेतला. या निर्णयामुळे पन्हाळा किल्ल्यावर शिवछत्रपतींचे स्मारक असावे अशी इच्छा बाळगणाऱ्या लाखो शिवप्रेमींची इच्छा पूर्ण होणार आहे. 

विधानभवनातील माझ्या दालनात आज कोल्हापूरमधील आमदारांची विशेष बैठक आज पार पडली. या बैठकीत कोल्हापूर जिल्ह्यातील  आमदारांची आणि लाखो शिवप्रेमींची ही मागणी मान्य करत शिवस्मारकाच्या कामासाठी निधी देण्याचा निर्णय घेऊन तसा जीआर आजच्या आज कोल्हापुरातील आमदारांच्या हाती सुपूर्द करण्यात आला. 

यावेळी आरोग्य मंत्री प्रकाश आबीटकर, आमदार राजेश क्षीरसागर, आमदार चंद्रदीप नरके, नगरविकास विभागाचे प्रधान सचिव असीम गुप्ता, उपमुख्यमंत्री कार्यालयाचे प्रधान सचिव नवीन सोना तसेच इतर वरिष्ठ अधिकारी उपस्थित होते.

#Kolhapur #EknathShinde #Maharashtra #chhatrapatishivajimaharaj

‘बीबीसी मराठी’ या डिजिटल वाहिनीच्या वतीने आयोजित करण्यात आलेल्या ‘राष्ट्र महाराष्ट्र’ या विशेष कार्यक्रमात सहभागी होऊन बीबीसी मराठीचे संपादक अभिजित कांबळे यांच्यासोबत राज्याच्या विकासाचे चित्र मांडले. 

महायुती सरकारच्या १०० दिवसांच्या कार्यकाळात सात सुत्रांवर आधारीत काम करून लोकांना दिलासा देण्याचा प्रयत्न केला असल्याचे याप्रसंगी सांगितले. कृषी, शिक्षण, आरोग्य, पायाभूत सुविधा, गुंतवणूक आणि लोककल्याणकारी योजना यांना प्राधान्य देऊन त्यानुसार निर्णय घेण्याचा प्रयत्न केला असल्याचे यासमयी सांगितले. 

आमच्यात कोणतीही स्पर्धा नसून मुख्यमंत्री आणि दोन्ही उपमुख्यमंत्री एकमेकांसोबत काम करत आहोत. त्यामुळे राज्य प्रगतीपथावर असून पायाभूत सुविधा, उद्योग आणि परकीय गुंतवणूक क्षेत्रात राज्य आज देशात आघाडीवर आहे. त्यामुळे जनतेने घरी बसवलेल्यांचा विचार न करता राज्याच्या सर्वांगीण विकासाला आम्ही प्राधान्य दिले असल्याचे याप्रसंगी स्पष्ट केले.

यावेळी बीबीसी मराठीचे पत्रकार विनायक गायकवाड, निलेश धोत्रे, दीपाली जगताप आणि संपादकीय टीमचे सर्व सदस्य उपस्थित होते.

#BBCMarathi #EknathShinde #Shivsena #Maharashtra
@bbcnewsmarathi @shivsenaofc

केंद्र आणि राज्य सरकार तसेच भाभा अनुविज्ञान संस्थेच्या पुढाकाराने साकारल्या जात असलेल्या ‘कांदा महाबँक’ या उपक्रमाचा आढावा घेण्यासाठी आज विधानभवनात विशेष बैठक पार पडली. 

या बैठकीत कांदा महाबँक स्थापन करण्यात येत असलेल्या अडचणी जाणून घेत त्या सोडवण्याचे निर्देश संबंधित अधिकाऱ्यांना दिले. तसेच अद्ययावत पध्दतीने करायच्या इरेडिकेशन प्रक्रियेसाठी लागणाऱ्या खर्चाचा आढावा घेऊन हा निधी उभारण्यासाठी कर्ज तसेच इतर पर्यायांचा अवलंब करण्यास सुचवले. 

यावेळी मित्रा संस्थेचे मुख्य कार्यकारी अधिकारी प्रवीण परदेशी, नगरविकास विभागाचे प्रधान सचिव असीम गुप्ता, एमएसआरडिसीचे व्यवस्थापकीय संचालक अनिलकुमार गायकवाड तसेच एमआयडीसी, भाभा अनुविज्ञान संस्था, हिंदुस्थान ऍग्रो आणि संबंधित विभागांचे वरिष्ठ अधिकारी उपस्थित होते.

#EknathShinde #Maharashtra #KandaMahabank

Selena Gomez and Benny Blanco join me on On Purpose to share their love story like never before — one filled with misreads, growth, laughter, and real connection. 

We talk about:

• How they stayed connected and built trust while dating in secret, long distance

• How their relationship only worked because they met at the right time in their lives

user_info.Images[9].Caption:
Comment “YES” and I’ll send todays episode with @selenagomez and @itsbennyblanco straight to you ❤️🎙️

Being with Selena and Benny left me feeling truly hopeful about love. In a world that often encourages us to protect, perform, or hold back — they choose to lead with vulnerability, honesty, and heart.

Selena, your grace has always been evident. But in this conversation, I saw something even deeper — your courage in remaining soft in a world that can be harsh. And that’s the real strength! The way you love, even after everything you’ve experienced, is a quiet kind of strength. Just by being yourself, you create space for others to do the same.

Benny, you model something we need more of — a love that is expressive, grounded, and intentional. You listen deeply, speak with purpose, and create safety in every interaction. The way you speak about Selena — with admiration, presence, and lightness — is a beautiful reflection of what true respect looks like.

What you’ve built together goes beyond romance. It’s rooted in friendship, honesty, growth, and ease. It’s not about perfection — it’s about presence. And because it’s real, it reminds people what’s possible.

That love can be gentle. And that’s what makes it strong. That it can be safe. That you don’t have to lose yourself to be fully loved.
Thank you both for your openness. Thank you for making love feel meaningful again.

Watch entire episode on YouTube right now by searching “On Purpose Selena Gomez and Benny Blanco”

Happy New Year, Everyone - 

Sadly, it has been brought to my attention that online scammers are intensifying their efforts to target my fans and supporters. As part of their tactics, they create multiple, deceptive social media and email accounts impersonating me and members of my team.

Today, AI can create the illusion of my face and voice. Scammers may look and sound just like the real me. But, neither I, nor my team, will ask you for money or your personal information.
 
We are actively working to combat these illicit schemes. While we do, for the protection and awareness of my fans, I am reiterating the following: 
 
• This page (@johnnydepp) is my only account on Instagram 
• My only Facebook account is @johnnydepp
• My only TikTok account is @johnnydepp
• I am not on X/Twitter, Snapchat, or Discord
 
• I do not offer paid meetings, phone calls, club memberships, or fan cards. If you are ever asked for any money for a meeting, call, membership, or fan card, it is a scam. 
 
• I do not interact directly with fans on any social media platforms, via email, or via chat-based platforms like Telegram, WhatsApp, Signal or Zangi.
 
• Again, neither myself, my team, my agent, nor my family will ever contact you on my behalf asking for money or your personal information.
 
JD and team.X

user_info.Images[0].Caption:
🕉 Today marks five years since our beloved Ram Dass left his body, merging fully into the infinite love he always embodied. 

In his honour, I am deeply humbled to share something close to my heart and very special. 

For over a decade, I’ve been working on a book with Ram Dass. It includes teachings on spirituality and is infused with the essence of his presence. 

The book is called 'Be Your Self'.

Be Your Self is an exploration of spirituality’s deepest truth—a journey into the freedom that transcends all boundaries, inviting us into the oneness that lives beyond differences.

The book includes ideas from the Vedas and my conversations with Ram Dass on the Upanishads. It carries forward Maharaji's message that we are all one.

To celebrate Ram Dass’s life and legacy, a special limited first edition will be released on his birthday, April 6th, 2025. Each copy will be signed with love.

If you feel called to join this sacred journey and would like to be notified, simply comment 'Yes' below, and we will add your name to the list.

With love, 

Hanuman Dass🙏

#beyourself

Go Dharmic is a movement of unconditional love and altruistic compassion. A community which acts for the welfare of all sentient beings and our planet.

user_info.Images[3].Caption:
So often, we chase after fleeting things,
small pleasures, achievements, possessions,
hoping they will fill the emptiness we feel.

But these are like small pools of water,
temporary and easily disturbed.

The Bhagavad Gita offers us a deeper truth:
What need is there for a small pool of water,
when water flows from every direction?

We are not the restless waves.
We are the ocean—still, deep, infinite. We are one with all beings. This is the essence of both spirituality and social action. 

Join me this evening as we explore the timeless wisdom of the Gita together.

The Journey Within
6pm GMT | Live on Zoom
All are welcome. Link in bio.

user_info.Images[8].Caption:
Neem Karoli Baba's words, Love all. Feed all. Serve all. Remember God are a guiding force.

Love all means extending compassion without discrimination. It’s easy to love people who treat us well, but the deeper challenge is to love those who are difficult, different, or even unkind. Love is not about agreement—it’s about recognising the divine in every being. It's about unconditional love. 

Feed all reminds us that nobody should go hungry. But hunger isn’t only physical. People are also hungry for kindness, for connection, for hope. Feeding others means offering what we can—food, time, encouragement, or simply presence.

Serve all is about humility. It means using our time and energy for the well-being of others. Service is not about status or recognition. It’s about doing what needs to be done, with sincerity and care.

Remember God grounds everything. It’s the call to stay inwardly connected while living outwardly engaged. To remember that behind every face, every act, and every moment, there is something sacred. We are all part of the divine. 

These words are not complicated. But living them fully transforms everything.

user_info.Images[2].Caption:
A woman wants to know if surrendering to God is the key to transmuting suffering in the world, and how that fits in with the message of Jesus on the cross.

Rupert says: ‘Jesus first resolved the issue of resistance within himself and then he turned towards the world, sharing that understanding with the people who were torturing him. Because when he resolved the issue of resistance within himself a transmutation took place – from sorrow to pure love.

‘Similarly you’ve surrendered your struggle with sorrow and you bear it in your heart.  And the reason you can bear it is because your heart is big enough – not only for your personal sorrow – but also humanity’s sorrow. Just as your sorrow is ultimately not personal, your heart, whose nature is love, is also not personal. It is the heart of infinite being whose nature is love – and that is what you are.’

Watch the full video on YouTube: https://youtu.be/pyckOdit3eg

user_info.Images[5].Caption:
In this conversation about the source of creation a woman asks about a passage from the Quran: ‘I was a hidden treasure and I loved to be known, so I created the world that I might be known.’ What does it mean?

Rupert says: ‘What I think it means is that within consciousness, there is infinite treasure or potential which in consciousness’s experience of itself remains unmanifest. There is just the knowledge “I am” – no world, or objective experience. 

‘But at the same time, that “I am” contains all knowledge and experience. It’s as if consciousness is pregnant with infinite potential – and it has to be born. So the birth of the universe is the means by which that which lies in potential in consciousness is made manifest.’

Watch the full video on YouTube.

user_info.Images[11].Caption:
Rupert mentions three recognitions regarding the nature of awareness: you are the witness of experience, you are that in which experience arises and you are one with experience. Why is the third recognition so much more difficult to grasp than the first two? 

Rupert says: ‘The reason why it’s relatively easy to understand the first two is that neither of them contradict the evidence of sense-perception. But the last recognition does. It completely shatters our conventional materialistic view of the world. 

‘And even when we understand this clearly, sense-perception still tells us the world is outside of our self, separate from our self, made out of something other than our self – and our understanding has to override that.’

#rupertspira #nonduality #nondualteachings #rupertspiravideo #nondualcommunity #spirituality

user_info.Images[0].Caption:
When I was a child playing cricket in the fields in Punjab, I had one dream. A dream to represent my country. In 2018, by Gods grace, I received my India Cap Number 75 in the T20i team and Cap Number 221 in the ODI team.

The time has now come to call time on my career in India and announce my retirement.

Words cannot express my gratitude for the love and support I have received through all the highs and lows of my career. I want to thank God for the path that has been made for me; the fans for the endless support; my parents and family for the sacrifices and confidence you have given me, especially during the injuries and lows; my teammates over the years for the dressing room memories and friendships; the BCCI for fulfilling a young child’s dream to represent India and win the 2008 Under-19 World Cup and receive my T20i and ODI caps in 2018!
Kolkata Knight Riders , Delhi Daredevils, Sunrisers Hyderabad and Royal Challengers Bangalore IPL franchises for giving me memories of a lifetime; and last but not least, the @pcacricketassociation for giving me an opportunity to make my First Class debut in 2007 and supporting me throughout my career. Without all your support I would not be the person I am today.

I don’t know what the future holds but I look back on this chapter with only fond memories and now on to the next chapter. 

Once again, thank you

Siddharthh Kaul 
(Sid Kaul)

user_info.Biography: Uncovering the world of Patek Philippe, the last independent, family-owned Genevan watch manufacture. Welcome. #PatekTime
user_info.Images[0].Caption:
The historic desk clocks made in the 1920s for renowned collectors James Ward Packard and Henry Graves Jr. are feature both key-winding and setting. Each clock features a 24’’’ eight-day going movement and seven horological complications. On top of the date of the month, day of the week and month of the year, the complications include a perpetual calendar with apertures, phases of the Moon, a four-year cycle of leap-years and an eight day power-reserve indication.

Both timepieces are housed in the Patek Philippe Museum, Geneva: Inv. P-140 (Packard) and Inv. P-1270 (Graves).

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMuseum #SuperComplications
user_info.Images[1].Caption:
In the early 1920s, Patek Philippe created two extraordinary desk clocks for renowned collectors James Ward Packard and Henry Graves Jr. respectively. Beyond their technical qualities and complications, the Packard clock (1923) and Graves clock (1927) stand as testaments to Patek Philippe's artistry with the hand-engraved details, painted numerals, metalwork and decorations.

These extraordinary pieces are part of the Patek Philippe Museum, Geneva: Inv. P-140 (Packard) and Inv. P-1270 (Graves).

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMuseum #SuperComplications
user_info.Images[2].Caption:
The great American collectors of the early twentieth century, James Ward Packard and Henry Graves Jr., are considered the most important individuals who changed the world of watch collecting. Packard was a self-made entrepreneur and inventor who was one of the pioneers of the automobile. Graves Jr., on the other hand, came from an affluent New York financial dynasty. 

They both commissioned specific timepieces based on their interests and personalities and, as such, challenged watchmakers. Among the myriad masterpieces created for these two collectors during the brief golden age was a wedge-shaped yellow gold and silver perpetual calendar moon-phase desk clock (Patek Philippe Museum, Geneva, Inv. No. P-140). It was delivered to James Ward Packard in 1923, and another almost identical model was sold by Tiffany & Co. to Henry Graves Jr. in 1927 (Patek Philippe Museum, Geneva, Inv. No. P-1270).

These historical timepieces are housed in the Patek Philippe Museum in Geneva.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMuseum #SuperComplications
user_info.Images[3].Caption:
The Service Center in Beijing is part of a global network of Authorized Service Centers, each handpicked and accredited based on achieving and maintaining a level of service that adheres to strict quality criteria.

A fundamental part of what Patek Philippe does, customer service involves taking care of the customers as individuals, with unique needs, whilst maintaining consistency in providing the highest level of support.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMaisons
user_info.Images[4].Caption:
The Maison Patek Philippe Beijing is located amid a historical enclave of consular residences at Ch’ien Men, one of the city’s most renowned cradles of culture and the arts. It stands as a strong symbol of the brand as reflected by the Maison's Chinese name, “Yuan Di” (“Yuan” means origin in English and “Di” is the translation of ‘Maison’).

The façade of the Maison maintains the neoclassical elegance of the building. The interior design, referencing the Patek Philippe Geneva Salons and the Maison Patek Philippe Shanghai, presents the brand's exquisite aesthetics and unique characteristics. The design creates a warm and welcoming atmosphere for guests to discover and experience the Patek Philippe collections.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMaisons
user_info.Images[5].Caption:
In 2008, Patek Philippe expanded its presence in China by opening a boutique in Beijing and subsequently in 2014 the Maison Patek Philippe Beijing, echoing the boutique and maison combination present in Shanghai. Located in the heart of the capital, it quickly became a refined destination for watch connoisseurs. To further nurture this legacy, the brand crafted an elegant and welcoming space, inviting enthusiasts of exceptional watchmaking.

Marking a significant milestone in Patek Philippe’s journey in China, the Maison in Beijing is comparable to the Patek Philippe Salons in Geneva, London, and Paris, both in status and function. It offers an unparalleled setting where guests can immerse themselves in the brand’s timeless artistry and unwavering commitment to service.

Every visit is an invitation to experience the enduring values that have defined Patek Philippe since 1839.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMaisons
user_info.Images[6].Caption:
The opening of Maison Patek Philippe in Shanghai in 2012 led to the expansion of the Service Center at Yifeng Galleria, with an independent space of nearly 1,000 square meters, perfectly equipped to accommodate 30 employees.

In September 2013, Patek Philippe reaffirmed its long-term investment and confidence in the Chinese market by inaugurating the Patek Philippe Institute Shanghai — its first training center outside Geneva. This institution was created to recruit and train local apprentices, ensuring that after-sales service meets the strict quality standards established by the Manufacture, in full compliance with the Patek Philippe Seal.

Today, the Shanghai Service Center remains one of only two Patek Philippe Authorized Service Centers in mainland China, a testament to the brand’s enduring pursuit of excellence.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMaisons
user_info.Images[7].Caption:
The Maison Patek Philippe Shanghai enjoys a prime location along the scenic Huangpu River, surrounded by Victorian and neoclassical buildings. This site holds a special place in Shanghai’s history, marking the city’s early development. The name “Maison” reflects its prestigious status, while “Yuan” (源) in Chinese means “origin” in English and signifies both its geographical origins and its role as a source of culture and heritage. The building itself, originally the residence of the British Consul General, carries a distinguished legacy.

The interior of Maison Patek Philippe Shanghai embodies the elegance of the Napoléon III style and recreates the refined atmosphere of Patek Philippe’s Geneva Salon.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMaisons
user_info.Images[8].Caption:
In 2005, Patek Philippe opened its first boutique in China in the historic Bund area of Shanghai. As Patek Philippe’s presence in China continued to flourish, a deeper appreciation for the brand grew within the country. In response, Patek Philippe created a warm and welcoming area, open to all watch aficionados.

As a landmark of Patek Philippe’s 20-year journey in China, the Maison in Shanghai holds a unique position in the world, comparable to the Patek Philippe Salons in Geneva, London, and Paris - presenting the brand’s collections in an exclusive setting, combined with an unwavering dedication to service.

Each visit offers guests the opportunity to experience the emotional connection that has defined Patek Philippe since its founding in 1839.

#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeMaisons
user_info.Images[9].Caption: Since 1995, the Paris Salons have stood at Place Vendôme, the city’s emblematic hub for 'haute horlogerie' and 'haute joaillerie'. With their Art Deco elegance, the Salons harmonize beautifully with the historic architecture of this iconic Parisian square.\n\n#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeSalons
user_info.Images[10].Caption: The Art Deco-style is reflected throughout the Paris Salons, in harmony between tradition and innovation. The Salons present the same combination of classicism and modernity as that of the Patek Philippe Salons in Geneva, with the same marriage of noble materials such as marble, alabaster and rosewood or maple wood. However, the space remains its own with particular emphasis on artistic ironwork, perfectly in line with the “Grand Siècle” architecture of Place Vendôme.\n\n#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeSalons
user_info.Images[11].Caption: The City of Light has a special significance for Patek Philippe. In 1844, Antoine Norbert de Patek first met Jean Adrien Philippe, in Paris, and a piece of history was made. Over a century later, in 1986, Philippe Stern (then President of Patek Philippe) opened the first Salons outside Geneva on Avenue Montaigne, marking a significant milestone in the company’s history. In 1995, they moved to Place Vendôme, Paris’ most emblematic landmark for 'haute horlogerie' and 'haute joaillerie', where it has remained ever since.\n\n#PatekTime #PatekPhilippeSalons

user_info.Biography: 150 years of horological mastery, bold design, passion and free-spirit. And the beat goes on. #AP150
user_info.Images[0].Caption:
Mastering complexity with ease. 
Calibre 7138 is the latest chapter of our legacy, combining functionality and aesthetics to achieve legibility and timeless refinement. Our Project Manager New Product Development, Nicolas Ponsot, invites you to discover the small details that make this complex mechanism.

Ref. 26674ST.OO.1320ST.01

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[1].Caption:
Innovative ergonomics.
Take a closer look to Calibre 7138 offering optimal legibility of the perpetual calendar functions. The Manufacture's new cutting-edge movement features three patented mechanisms and is adjusted solely with the crown, removing the need for additional tools. Set the date, month, time, leap year, and moonphase with just four positions. 

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[2].Caption:
Who said complications couldn’t be this easy? 
Set the date, month, time, leap year, and moonphase with just four positions thanks to Calibre 7138’s crown correction. Head of Complications, Anne-Gaëlle Quinet, breaks it down into five steps (and shares the oops moments you’ll want to avoid).

The first position winds the watch clockwise and the second one sets the date and adjusts the month and the leap year in the opposite direction. Position three sets the time bidirectionally. Lastly, position four—one step back—sets the day and week clockwise and the moon phases counterclockwise.

Ref. 26494BC.OO.D350KB.01

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[3].Caption:
Legacy written in the stars.
Since 1875, astronomical complications have been at the heart of Audemars Piguet. Beginning with our founders’ school pocket watches, our timepieces have long reflected a tradition of astronomical craftsmanship, inspired by the clear night skies of the Vallée de Joux. Calibre 7138 is the latest evolution of this heritage.

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[4].Caption:
Effortless complexity.
By integrating ergonomics in the development of the new perpetual calendar, we’ve created a unique correction mechanism that allows all adjustments via the crown, making this high complication not only user-friendly but effortless. Combined with a refined aesthetic, it offers both exceptional legibility and timeless elegance.

Ref. 26494BC.OO.D350KB.01

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[5].Caption:
A dial combining legibility with aesthetic harmony.
Our new perpetual calendar watches features a harmonious dial layout with the day, date, and month thoughtfully positioned for optimal legibility. With a patented date disc and a 24-hour indicator in perfect symmetry, this timepiece is a true celebration of design and precision.

Ref. 26674SG.OO.1320SG.01
Ref. 26494BC.OO.D350KB.01

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[6].Caption:
A calibre blending tradition with innovation.
Celebrating 150 years of innovation, Calibre 7138 represents our commitment to craftsmanship. After 5 years of development, this perpetual calendar introduces an intuitive crown, merging advanced functionality with cutting-edge ergonomics. 
A milestone in horological history, redefining the experience of timekeeping for everyday wear. 

Ref. 26674SG.OO.1320SG.01
Ref. 26494BC.OO.D350KB.01

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[7].Caption:
A tribute to the universe and craftsmanship.
Since the dawn of time, the moon and stars have guided us, shaping our understanding of time. From ancient sundials to the intricate perpetual calendar, watchmakers have tirelessly crafted mechanisms that connect us to the universe’s rhythm. 
Our new perpetual calendar watch opens up new technical and design avenues with ergonomics at heart to adapt to evolving lifestyles.

Ref. 26674SG.OO.1320SG.01

#AudemarsPiguet #AP150
user_info.Images[8].Caption:

Introducing Calibre 7138, a new generation of selfwinding perpetual calendar with revolutionary ergonomics at its core. All the corrections of all functions are now possible through its “all-in-one” crown.

One movement, three aesthetics:

user_info.Images[10].Caption:
Let the year of celebration begin!
True to the spirit that shaped us, a century and a half later, we are still that village, still those villagers, embarked on an extraordinary journey.

user_info.Images[3].Caption: 🕉️ राम राम , Ma Maharaj ji ki Jai! Bala Saini, and my husband, Shri Kisan Chand Saini, with our whole family went to Nainital in 1974. Some friends of my father along with their families were with us. We all reached Kainchi ashram where Shri Ma gave us darshan. After the darshan, we got prasad. Then Shri Ma called us and said to my father, “Saini take these Maharaj Ji’s picture lockets” and said “put it on this child just now”, “what is your name, your daughter is very adorable”. Then Ma, with Her own hands, put on Maharaj Ji’s locket for me.\nThen we all went to Nainital. In Nainital, me and my brother Satish, both told our father we wanted to go for horse riding. Father agreed. On the way some naughty girl distracted my horse with a stick. The horse went out of control and started running at a high speed. The horse took me on a high mountain and threw me down. On one side was the lake and on the other a mountain. Because of Ma’s Blessings I fell towards the mountain side and didn’t get even a scratch. My eyes closed and I fainted. Just then my father and his friends came and took me in a car to a hospital. There the doctor gave me an injection and  medicine. In a few hours I became conscious. Then we all left for Kainchi and reached the Kainchi Ashram by evening around 6:00p.m. Ma was standing in front of our room in the verandah. In Her hands She was holding a hot water bottle and She immediately made me lie down on Her lap and started doing hot compress with the hot water bottle. Then She gave me water with Her hands and I became alright. Ma is an extension of Maharaj ji. Ma on many occasions has brought us out of innumerable difficulties with Her Blessings - Sri Bala Saini - Eternal Bond , सिया राम 🙏
user_info.Images[4].Caption: 🕉️ राम राम , Maharaj addressed the murti at the Hanuman temple in Rambag, Allahabad, as the “Controller General.” One day Sri Ma was at the temple with Maharaj and saw an old woman climbing the stairs with great difficulty to have the darshan of Hanuman, who was on the first floor. She felt great pity for the woman and drew Baba’s attention to her. Baba asked the manager, “Why cannot Hanuman-ji come down? Mothers find it difficult to go up the stairs.” The manager and the priest of the temple knew Baba, but the manager said that since the murti had been installed up-stairs, nothing could be done about it. Baba heard this and left.\nHe had only asked a question, but God’s will is supreme and must be materialised. Shortly thereafter it rained so heavily that the back portion of the old temple, where the murti had been installed, collapsed. The rest of the temple remained intact and undamaged. When the back walls collapsed, the murti descended to the ground floor in a standing position, as if Hanuman-ji had been carefully placed there. The murti was not damaged at all. Keeping Hanuman-ji there on the ground floor, the whole temple was reconstructed around him. - it All Abides in love By Jai Ram Ransom Sir , सिया राम 🙏

user_info.Images[6].Caption: 🕉️ राम राम , My Mother was a devotee of Hanuman ji from childhood; she worshiped Him and had complete faith in Him. Whenever she had any problem she would tell Hanuman Ji. Perhaps it was because of this that she got Hanuman Ji, in the form of Maharaj, in her life. One day, lja asked Maharaj. “everyone calls you Hanuman ji, are you Hanuman? Why can’t I see?” He answered, “there is a stone in your eye.” Now what did that mean? Once He started saying, “Whatever I have done for you, I will tell you after I leave this body. You will stand in one witness box and I will be in another, there only I will answer.” In fact, if we come to know how the Guru is standing behind us every moment to protect us, then we cannot survive. Kripalu Maharaj had said, “It is only after attaining God that one comes to know that it is the Guru who has done everything. If you come to know about it earlier, you will not be able to bear it, the heart will fail.” - The Eternal Bond , सिया राम 🙏
user_info.Images[7].Caption: 🕉️ राम राम , SUIL: When we went to Kainchi on the bus, we passed this house, and I went, “Oh, I want to stay there.” It turned out the owners of that house, both doctors in Nainital, were from Scotland, from my same town. That was the house I wound up staying in. The flower garden there was almost like a nursery. You could go down the back road through all of those flowers, through the rivers, through the mountains, and end up at the rear of the ashram. One morning I collected a bunch of flowers and came in through the back of the ashram. It turned out everyone had been jaoed except Larry and Girija. Maharajji called me over, and I gave him the flowers. What I heard him say to me, and what stayed in my mind for a long time, was, “Every flower blooms in its own time.” I didn’t have a very strong identity, and I wasn’t really sure who I was in all of this. It was the first time I was living alone, in the mountains with the monkeys. So when he said that statement about all flowers blooming in their own time, I felt relief knowing that I didn’t have to be concerned if I was okay, if I was going to be a saint or not. Many years later at a bandhara I met Larry again. We were remembering that story with the flowers, and what Larry remembered was a completely different story. He had heard Maharajji say that all the flowers bloom at the same time. Really? I was sure he said in their own time. We talked about which version we liked better. I was glad that I heard my version, because that was very helpful in my whole journey. Even today, that idea that the timing of everything is really perfect, that there is a perfection in everything, and as the flowers bloom so shall we . . . There’s been an ease that came in that story, and that was something I would never forget, in a very simple statement that other people heard differently, of course. We love that. - Love  Everyone by Parvati Markus ma’am , सिया राम 🌸
user_info.Images[8].Caption:
🕉️ राम राम , The inauguration of the temple was to be celebrated in the most fitting manner, with pujas, havans, and prasad for everyone. The news
spread over a very large part of that area and people started coming. Everyone worked with a missionary zeal, and was convinced that their
preparations for the bhandara, which was soon to begin, were faultless. There was a sense of jubilation in having managed a difficult task,
and a few of them started speculating about the laurels that were awaiting them.
When Babaji arrived that evening, everyone joined in giving him an account of the work that had been completed. Every detail was given.
The prasad that had been prepared was enough to feed any unknown number of visitors. They then took Babaji around to see for himself all
that had been described. Babaji was pleased, and sat and listened with great satisfaction as they talked about their arrangements for feeding
people. Then, as if to get a minor clarification, he wanted to know on what they were going to serve the food. It was as if people who had
been going along, merrymaking on the road, suddenly got pushed into a ditch. Not one of them had remembered to get leaf plates!
What could be done at this short notice? People had started gathering, and feeding was to start within a few hours. There was no market
nearby. Haldwani and Bareilly were far away and the markets there would be closed for the night. It was hard to accept that a big engine
could not start if even a small part of strategic importance was missing. Gone was the cheer and jubilation—everyone was motionless. One
could imagine, on a much larger scale, how the monkeys had sat on the shore of the sea after losing all hope of success in their search for
Sita.
Babaji sat silently with them. Seeing him like that, many became disturbed and started making all kinds of speculations about his silence. It
was his bhandara. They had been pushed into it by him. They were there only because of him, but now that they were faced with such a
crisis, he was sitting indifferently. They might be responsible, but why should they be punished when he could remove their crisis? - Continued in Comments
user_info.Images[9].Caption: 🕉️ राम राम , I heard Krishna Das sing “Mere Gurudev” for the first time some sixteen years ago when I attended a Reiki seminar. My life was a mess. I felt sad, depressed, and anxious all the time, and I was consumed by anger from my child-hood. When I heard his voice, I felt something shift in me for the first time in years. Of course, I attributed my feeling of relief to my Reiki teacher, but I kept listening to Krishna Das and suddenly chants from my childhood started coming back to me. I remembered that my grandma used to chant every day. In January 2015, I attended a workshop that Krishna Das conducted in Mumbai. I had always seen a picture of Baba whenever Krishna Das sang, but I had no curiosity to know more about the man in the picture. A few days later, as is my practice each morning, I walked around a park while chanting along with Krishna Das on my phone. Suddenly my phone pinged and Maharaji’s photo popped up. I could not stop looking at him. I felt like I had definitely seen him before. A few days later I started getting attracted to the Hanuman Chalisa, which gave me such solace. I live with my husband and son. My mother-in-law, who was bedridden for the last five years of her life, also lived with us. She was the kindest, most loving person I had ever met, and I viewed her as my mother. I started chanting the Chalisa for her and she said that it brought her such peace. We chanted together every morning and evening. One day I was walking in the morning, chanting as usual. The park in which I walk has a Hanuman Temple. I passed the temple and suddenly, from the opposite direction, there was a huge beautiful golden monkey walking right towards me, looking straight at me. His eyes were almost human. This is not the kind of monkey we see in a city like Mumbai. - Continued In Comments Part 1 & 2
user_info.Images[10].Caption: 🕉️ राम राम , We think we are running after the Guru, but he is actually running after us. Why does he do it?  He is not fond of your money he is not fond of the sweet or nice things you talk about him; he is not fond of the publicity you can make about him. It is out of sheer grace, out of sheer kindness. You must know that a sage or a saint has got the whole wealth of the world at his disposal. He has got no needs, no requirements of his own. He doesn’t worry about food, clothes, money, nothing of the sort. A Guru is there to carry the big loads or burdens of his disciples. This is what the Guru goes on doing, giving and giving and giving to you. That giving we cannot call charity, which is a word that comes from our family references, our business life, our day-to-day life. A gift or charity is made to one from whom we have received something in the past or hope to get something in the future. When a gift is given, the relationship between the person making the gift and receiving it comes to be one superior and the other inferior. Somebody who goes on receiving charity, getting gifts, can never himself be very proud or very happy. But in the case of grace, anybody who has got the grace of God feels himself so elevated. “Oh, I have become something divine. I have been elevated.” So when the grace of the Guru comes, its purpose is to elevate, to raise and lift people. Now we know that a sage or a saint does not want anything, he has no need of his own, but still, out of grace, he makes you work for him, makes you give to him. A Guru comes to have a claim not only on your physical labor and exertion, but also on the working of your mind and on every possession. Tan- man-dhan [body-mind-wealth]. Your Guru can claim it all. In India, when you go to a temple and the priest performs a puja or any kind of prayer or ceremony, you must pay him a fee. You might also give prasad, rich clothes and ornaments to the deity, but if you don’t pay the priest, your worship is not complete. Similarly, a Guru is taking a lump of clay and turning it into something permanent and beautiful and abiding. - Continued in comments part 1 , 2 & 3
user_info.Images[11].Caption: 🕉️ राम राम , One late afternoon the devotees were sitting around Maharaj-ji. It was quiet, the sun was setting, birds were singing, and we were enjoying the beauty of the evening. I’d just noted to myself how peaceful this all was when he turned to me and said, “Watch this.” He asked a simple question in a very soft voice, like, “Is the weather warm in America?” All at once, the group erupted. Somebody said, “It depends on where you are.” Another started talking about the various regions, and another about the seasons. People started arguing with each other—it was chaos! Then he casually looked over at me with a mischievous smile, as if to say, See, you thought it was peaceful. But this is what it’s really like just under the surface. Maharaj-ji played with us to draw us out of our shells and into the love, because it is the power of that loving that makes it possible to overcome the feeling of being separate and alone. Every time I got lost in my thoughts, all I had to do was come back, and there he was. - Chants of a lifetime by krishna das ji , सिया राम 🙏

user_info.Images[11].Caption:
APPEAL
 
On the evening of Thursday 17th October a number of masked people burgled my home in the Castle Eden area in the North East.
 
They escaped with jewellery, other valuables and a good deal of personal items. Many of those items have real sentimental value for me and my family.  They are irreplaceable.
 
This is an appeal for any help in finding these people who carried out this act.
 
By far the worst thing about this crime is that it was carried out whilst my wife and 2 young children were in the house. Thankfully, none of my family came to any physical harm. Understandably, however, the experience has had an impact on their emotional and mental state. All we can think about is how much worse this situation could have been.
 
I am releasing photographs of some of the stolen items - which I hope may be easily identified - in the hope that we can find the people who are responsible for this.
 
Although we have lost cherished possessions, to be clear, my sole motivation in sharing these photographs is not the recovery of material items. It is to catch the people who did this.
 
Please come forward and contact Durham Constabulary on 101 quoting crime reference CRI00575927 if you think that you have any relevant information.
 
Finally, I want to say thank you to the police service. Both now and whilst I was away in Pakistan, their support for my family has been outstanding.  They continue to work incredibly hard in trying to find these people.
 
✌️ Stokes Fam

user_info.Images[10].Caption:
A bit late but thoroughly enjoyed the বাংলা commentary for @jiohotstar for my first icc event as a commentator. Was so happy to see the response & tweets coming in from the listeners. I along with my fellow commentators tried to make it fun along with the analysis for the viewer . 

Adding last bit - credit to the entire support staff for doing a incredible job with this bunch of talented Indian squad ! A lot of times we don’t give enough credit to people who work behind the scenes. 

একটু দেরিতে হলেও ধারাভাষ্যকার হিসেবে আমার প্রথম আইসিসি ইভেন্টে @jiohotstar-এর “বাংলা” ধারাভাষ্যটি উপভোগ করলাম। শ্রোতাদের কাছ থেকে প্রতিক্রিয়া এবং টুইটগুলি দেখে খুব খুশি হলাম। আমি এবং আমার সহকর্মী ধারাভাষ্যকাররা দর্শকদের জন্য বিশ্লেষণের পাশাপাশি এটিকে মজাদার করার চেষ্টা করেছি। 

শেষ অংশে যোগ করছি - এই প্রতিভাবান ভারতীয় দলের সাথে অবিশ্বাস্য কাজ করার জন্য সমগ্র সহায়তা কর্মীদের কৃতিত্ব! অনেক সময় আমরা পর্দার আড়ালে কাজ করা লোকদের যথেষ্ট কৃতিত্ব দেই না।

user_info.Images[3].Caption:
Some films find their audience in time…

Sandeep Aur Pinky Faraar—a film I chose to do four years ago, a film that pushed me out of my comfort zone and even surprised me as an actor. Back then, it didn’t get the love it truly deserved. Some praised it, but many missed out—maybe the timing wasn’t right, maybe it wasn’t what they expected.

Yesterday, the film completed four years, and seeing people still discover it, appreciate its layered storytelling, performances, and writing—it feels special. Some films age like fine wine, and this one seems to be getting its due credit now.

For those who haven’t watched it yet, Sandeep Aur Pinky Faraar is streaming on @primevideoin. 

It’s a film the entire team poured their hearts into, and it deserves all the love. Go watch it and give it the appreciation it was always meant to have. 💙

@parineetichopra @neena_gupta @jaideepahlawat @raghubir_y @yrf @primevideoin  #DibakarBanerjee #SandeepAurPinkyFaraar
